org.gbif.registry.ws.model

Class LegacyEndpoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.api.model.registry.Endpoint
      • org.gbif.registry.ws.model.LegacyEndpoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.gbif.api.model.registry.LenientEquals<org.gbif.api.model.registry.Endpoint>, org.gbif.api.model.registry.MachineTaggable

    public class LegacyEndpoint
extends org.gbif.api.model.registry.Endpoint
    Class used to create or update an Endpoint for legacy (GBRDS/IPT) API. Previously known as a Service in the GBRDS. A set of HTTP Form parameters coming from a POST request are injected.
    Its fields are injected using the @FormParam. It is assumed the following parameters exist in the HTTP request: 'resourceKey', 'description', 'descriptionLanguage', 'type', 'accessPointURL'.
    JAXB annotations allow the class to be converted into an XML document, that gets included in the Response following a successful registration or update. @XmlElement is used to specify element names that consumers of legacy services expect to find.
